author: Jonathan Allen
title: Trump sees ghosts of hometown past and election future in COVID-19
description: Analysis: President Donald Trump says he did more than nothing to stop the spread of coronavirus as he warns Americans that the coming week will be painful.
content:
If he had done nothing at all, President Donald Trump said Tuesday, the American death toll from the coronavirus would be geometrically higher than the low six-figure count he now expects.
In other words, it could have been worse.
